EXTENSION COMMAND

Create command:

"Copilot: Generate Intelligent Integration Tests"

When executed the extension must first ask the user to choose a data source.

Use VS Code QuickPick with two options:

• Local Log File
• Splunk Traces

--------------------------------------------------

WORKFLOW OPTION 1 — LOCAL LOG FILES

If user selects Local Log File:

1 ask user to select a log file
2 parse the log file
3 extract HTTP interactions
4 group interactions by traceId
5 reconstruct service flows

--------------------------------------------------

WORKFLOW OPTION 2 — SPLUNK TRACES

If user selects Splunk Traces:

1 ask user for Splunk query or traceId
2 call Splunk REST API
3 retrieve distributed traces
4 extract service flows
5 convert traces into interaction objects

Mock the Splunk API initially but design the module so it can call Splunk later.

--------------------------------------------------

COMMON PROCESSING STEPS

After collecting interaction data from either source:

1 scan workspace source code
2 perform AST scanning
3 extract endpoints and dependencies
4 build service dependency graph
5 combine

logs or traces  
AST data  
service dependencies

--------------------------------------------------

LOG PARSER

Implement logParser.ts.

Extract

timestamp  
traceId  
service name  
HTTP method  
URL  
request body  
response status  
response body  

Return HttpInteraction objects.

--------------------------------------------------

SPLUNK TRACE MODULE

Implement splunkTraceParser.ts.

Responsibilities

connect to Splunk REST API  
retrieve distributed traces  
map traceId to services  

Example response

{
 traceId:"123",
 services:["gateway","auth-service","payment-service"]
}

--------------------------------------------------

AST CODE SCANNER

Implement

javaAstScanner.ts  
nodeAstScanner.ts

Responsibilities

scan code repository  
detect REST endpoints  
detect outbound service calls  
detect dependencies

Return metadata

{
 service:"",
 endpoints:[],
 dependencies:[]
}

--------------------------------------------------

DEPENDENCY GRAPH

Implement dependencyGraph.ts.

Represent services as nodes and edges.

Example

gateway → auth-service  
gateway → payment-service  
payment-service → bank-api  

--------------------------------------------------

FLOW RECONSTRUCTION

Implement interactionBuilder.ts.

Group interactions by traceId.

Sort by timestamp.

Return ordered service call flows.

--------------------------------------------------

COPILOT PROMPT BUILDER

Implement copilotPromptBuilder.ts.

Build prompts sent to GitHub Copilot.

Prompt must include:

service dependency graph  
log or trace interactions  
API endpoints  

Example prompt

"Analyze the following microservice interactions and generate integration test scenarios using WireMock. Identify required mocks and produce test steps."

--------------------------------------------------

COPILOT AGENT

Implement copilotAgent.ts.

Responsibilities

send prompt to GitHub Copilot Chat API  
retrieve generated scenarios  
parse response  

--------------------------------------------------

TEST GENERATION

Use Copilot generated scenarios to produce:

WireMock stub files  
JUnit integration tests  

Example structure

@SpringBootTest
@AutoConfigureWireMock(port = 8089)

class PaymentFlowTest {

@Test
void testPaymentFlow(){

stubFor(post("/payment")
 .willReturn(okJson("{"status":"SUCCESS"}")));

}

}

--------------------------------------------------

